%I A397886 #8 Jul 16 2026 08:13:56
%S A397886 3,5,5,7,7,67,67,67,19256557,19256557,3349352911
%N A397886 The smallest number k such that the digit reversals of k, when written in all bases 2 to n, are prime.
%C A397886 a(13) <= A228768(13) = 14322793967831.
%F A397886 a(n) >= a(n-1).
%e A397886 a(7) = 67 as 67 = 124_7 = 151_6 = 232_5 = 1003_4 = 2111_3 = 1000011_2 whose digit reversals are 421_7 = 211, 151_6 = 67, 232_5 = 67, 3001_4 = 193, 1112_3 = 41, 1100001_2 = 97, and 211, 67, 193, 41, 97 are all prime. No smaller number satisfies this criterion.
%Y A397886 Cf. A228768, A397950, A000040, A004086.
%K A397886 nonn,base,more,new
%O A397886 2,1
%A A397886 _Scott R. Shannon_, Jul 14 2026
